Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine rose-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with star symbols.
Curator's comments: Name Aristarchos. Trimmed. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0031.09?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0889)
